{"issuance_frequency":"","notes_translated":{"fr":"Ce que nous avons trouvé\r\n\r\nLes jeunes ont relevé que les facteurs les plus importants dont les juges devraient tenir compte lorsqu’ils infligent des peines justes et équitables sont les circonstances personnelles et les antécédents de l’accusé, la nature de l’infraction, y compris le contexte, la gravité et les motifs de l’infraction. En définitive, les jeunes ne croient pas que les peines minimales obligatoires (PMO) sont avantageuses, car elles restreignent le pouvoir discrétionnaire des juges.","en":"What we found:\r\n\r\nYoung people noted that the most important factors judges should consider in fair and equitable sentencing are personal circumstances and history of the accused person, and the nature of the crime, including the context, severity and motive for the crime. Ultimately, young people did not believe that mandatory minimum penalties (MMPs) were beneficial because they limit judicial discretion."},"issn":"","imso_approval":"true","isbn":"","creator":"","org_section":{"fr":"","en":""},"jurisdiction":"federal","private":false,"maintainer_email":"open_Government@justice.gc.ca","num_tags":0,"edition":"","frequency":"as_needed","data_series_issue_identification":{"fr":"","en":""},"contributor":{"fr":"","en":""},"maintainer":null,"ready_to_publish":"true","id":"4247c11c-50c6-4c6c-9e25-92a542779a33","metadata_created":"2018-11-20T19:02:07.463242","subject":["law","persons"],"pspc_identification_number":"","metadata_modified":"2018-11-20T19:02:07.463252","author":null,"author_email":null,"geographic_region":[],"portal_release_date":"2018-11-20","digital_object_identifier":"","state":"active","version":null,"keywords":{"fr":["Décision du tribunal","Recherche","Système judiciaire","Juge","Justice pénale","Jeunesse"],"en":["Court decisions","Research","Justice system","judges","Criminal justice","Youth"]},"relationships_as_object":[],"creator_user_id":"4cfa9a9c-1d95-40eb-86f9-bc0c8ec45d1f","title_translated